In [212]:
#Imputer les valeur manquantes

def Imput_ValeurManquate ( Data, columns_Num, Imput_Num= "median") :
    for col in columns_Num :
        if Imput_Num == "median" :
            Change = np.median(Data[col].dropna()) 
        else:  
            Change = int(Imput_Num)
        Data[col] = Data[col].fillna(Change)
   
    return(Data)

In [215]:
#cible et choix colonnes 
def DataModel(features , Data , label) :
    Train = Data[features]
    if label in Data.columns :
        label = Data[label]
        return Train, label
        
    return Train

X_train, X_test,y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.33, random_state=42)

#construction du model
Reg_Log = linear_model.LogisticRegression(random_state=42)

#Apprentissage du model
Reg_Log.fit(X_train, y_train)

#Prediction du model
ypred = Reg_Log.predict(X_test)

log_loss = metrics.accuracy_score(y_test , ypred)

from matplotlib import style
style.use('fivethirtyeight')
%matplotlib inline
%pylab inline



def PlotHist(X1, X2, feature) :
    # plot histograms
    x1 = np.array(X1[feature].dropna())
    x2 = np.array(X2[feature].dropna())
    plt.hist([x1, x2], label=["High", "Medium"], bins=18, color=['b', 'r'])
       
    # add title and legend to the plot
    plt.title("Distribution des Niveaux des Joueurs par %s" %feature )
    plt.legend(loc="upper left")
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
